article.description: Sam Sessoms had 26 points as Binghamton beat Stony Brook 78-72 in the quarterfinals of the America East Conference Tourney on Saturday night.
article.headline: Binghamton upsets Stony Brook 78-72 in America East tourney
article.linkText: Binghamton upsets Stony Brook 78-72 in America East tourney
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- Sam Sessoms had 26 points as Binghamton beat Stony Brook 78-72 in the quarterfinals of the America East Conference Tourney on Saturday night. J.C. Show had 19 points for Binghamton (10-22). Caleb Stewart added 16 points and three blocks. Calistus Anyichie had seven rebounds for the visitors. Elijah Olaniyi had 27 points and nine rebounds for the Seawolves (24-8). Jaron Cornish added 13 points. Akwasi Yeboah had 13 points and seven rebounds. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
